&lt;p&gt;Consultant Neurologist with Specialist Interest in MS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Full time, Substantive)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neurology Department of North Bristol NHS Trust is looking to appoint a full time Consultant Neurologist with Interest in MS Neuroinflammatory. The successful applicant will join growing team of Consultant Neurologists to provide general outpatients services as well as specialist clinics. The post holder will run clinics at state of the art Brunel Building of Southmead Hospital as well as other locations (Bristol Brain Centre).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Neurology is a part of the Regional Neurosciences Centre and provides all inpatient specialist neurology services for Bristol and adjacent area, including 24 hour emergency neurology and acute neurology cover. The Department provides outreach neurology clinics and a consultative service for local DGHs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be on the GMC Specialist Register or within 6 months of attaining Specialist Registration at the time of interview. Applications from candidates who, for personal reasons, are unable to work full-time will be eligible to be considered for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
